    "body": "## Purpose\n\nWhen dequantizing weights with the `eye` method, the static scaling factor may actually push the 1s out of float8 range.\n\nDon't use that method when there's static scaling factors.\n\n## Test Plan\n\n## Test Result\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Addresses weight dequantization overflow with static per‑tensor FP8 scaling and centralizes logic.\n> \n> - Add `get_attribute_fallback` and `get_and_maybe_dequant_weights` in `quant_utils.py` to retrieve weights and dequantize safely (handles unquantized, FP8 block/tensor scales; falls back to eye-based path only as generic case)\n> - Update `scaled_dequantize` to return a single tensor (removed extra return)\n> - Replace ad-hoc dequantization in MLA `process_weights_after_loading` with the new utility and propagate `act_dtype`\n> - Minor typing/import tweaks (TYPE_CHECKING)\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 677db96ac17f2db481ed2f371de3fae1b66da21c. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Addresses FP8 static per‑tensor overflow and consolidates weight dequantization logic.\n> \n> - Add `get_attribute_fallback` and `get_and_maybe_dequant_weights` in `quant_utils.py` to retrieve and dequantize weights (handles unquantized, FP8 tensor/block scales; falls back to eye-path only as generic case)\n> - Update `scaled_dequantize` to return a single tensor\n> - Replace ad‑hoc dequantization in MLA `process_weights_after_loading` with the new utility and pass through `act_dtype`\n> - Minor typing/import adjustments (e.g., `TYPE_CHECKING`)\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 3d3d19271b700b4160c13e7fdce94e59f6d17d0e. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Consolidates and hardens FP8 weight dequantization, reducing overflow risk and removing ad‑hoc logic.\n> \n> - Adds `get_attribute_fallback` and `get_and_maybe_dequant_weights` in `quant_utils.py` to fetch and safely dequantize linear weights (handles unquantized, FP8 tensor/block scales; falls back to eye-based path only as generic case)\n> - Changes `scaled_dequantize` to return a single tensor\n> - Replaces custom MLA `process_weights_after_loading` dequantization with the new utility and propagates `act_dtype`\n> - Minor typing/import cleanup (e.g., `TYPE_CHECKING`)\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit a294947c2d519d6160309fa639b16887dde502ba. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> <sup>[Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) is generating a summary for commit f61fceec1f686da2c645a1680eef75fb44f982ba. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Consolidates and hardens FP8 weight dequantization to reduce overflow risk and remove ad‑hoc logic.\n> \n> - Adds `get_attribute_fallback` and `get_and_maybe_dequant_weights` in `quant_utils.py` to fetch and safely dequantize linear weights (handles unquantized, FP8 tensor/block scales; falls back to eye-based path only as a generic case)\n> - Changes `scaled_dequantize` to return a single tensor (API tweak)\n> - Replaces custom MLA `process_weights_after_loading` dequantization with `get_and_maybe_dequant_weights` and propagates `act_dtype`\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 4b8aaf13c87397945f8a8cc1105e7319a82b754f. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n",
